own<\/h2><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>Call us on: <a style=\"color: blue;\" href=\"tel:0832436483\">083 243 6483<\/a><\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>Dry Ice International is proud to deliver high density, high quality dry ice to meet every customer\u2019s need, directly to their specific location.<\/p><p>Dry Ice International delivers to your doorstep. Take a look at our prices on <em><strong>dry ice for sale in Cape Town<\/strong><\/em>, for any occasion, for every application of industrial and recreational use.<\/p><p>We are the largest supplier and manufacturer of dry ice in South Africa.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><\/div><div class=\"script_col\"><\/div><\/div><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>Shop a Selection of Dry Ice for Sale in Cape Town<\/h2><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>There is no need to continue your search for a dry ice supplier. Here at Dry Ice International, we have food grade dry ice and polystyrene containers. Dry ice is a flexible and often necessary component and is available in various shapes and sizes. Our dry ice products are capable of not only living up to your expectations but also satisfying any specialized requirements that you may have.<\/p><p>We also offer <a style=\"color: blue;\" href=\"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/polystyrene-containers\/\">polystyrene containers<\/a> and <a style=\"color: blue;\" href=\"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/cooler-boxes\/\">cooler boxes for sale<\/a>.<\/p><p>Dry Ice International offers dry ice for sale in Cape Town in different quantities, all of which are available for delivery anywhere in the city. Due to our staff&#8217;s extensive experience and training, we can offer a comprehensive selection of products and assistance. We can guarantee that our dry ice will last longer, making our dry ice line of products ideal for the warm South African climate.<\/p><p>Founded in 1994, Dry Ice International has secured a presence in the city of Cape Town. Through hard work, we have established ourselves as the industry standard for supplying dry ice. Dry ice is produced in-house by our company. In addition to the service of distribution, we also offer dry ice blasting to our clients.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>Preserving and Cooling<\/h2><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>The most typical use for dry ice is in the field of temperature control. Due to its exceptionally low temperature, dry ice may be used to swiftly cool and retain perishable commodities such as fruits, meats, and vegetables, as well as frozen meals, at ideal temperatures. This makes dry ice a perfect cooling option during an expected or unexpected power outage.<\/p><p>Additionally, it is a suitable option for the purpose of creating a thermal environment that is stable for the storage of temperature-sensitive drugs and medical supplies. If you need to transport medication but do not have access to a refrigerator, this is an excellent choice for you.<\/p><p>Cape Town is one of the busiest ports in South Africa, with so much cargo entering and departing the city on a daily basis, ensuring that you have an appropriate supply of dry ice is one of the most essential steps that your business can take.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>Cleaning<\/h2><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>Blasting with dry ice is a powerful cleaning method, despite the product&#8217;s more well-known application of keeping things cold. Dry ice blasting is quite similar to sandblasting, with the exception that dry ice pellets are used as opposed to sand. The dry ice method leaves no residue behind making it a cleaner and environmentally friendly way of cleaning<\/p><p>The city of Cape Town is home to several factories and warehouses, making sanitation a top priority and a formidable challenge without the proper equipment. Dry ice blasting is a versatile way to clean that can be used on a wide range of surfaces without damaging them or leaving any residue from the product itself.<\/p><p>As dry ice pellets revert back into gas, dry ice blasting is a necessary method for cleaning industrial equipment, including electric motors, electrical panels, and generators. As a result, cleaning virtually any environment with dry ice in Cape Town is a great alternative.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>Events<\/h2><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>If you want your event to stand out, dry ice may be exactly what you need. The misting of an area, the creation of sculptures, and the generation of vapor in drinking glasses are just a few of the many uses for dry ice.<\/p><p>If you are looking for a straightforward method to maintain the cool temperature of food and beverages, then dry ice is an absolute must.<\/p><p>Should you be interested in learning how to use dry ice, contact Dry Ice International, we offer everything you could possibly want to get started. We facilitate our customers&#8217; access to dry ice in Cape Town and provide a wealth of other resources and information. If you have any questions or would like to place an order, feel free to call or visit our website today.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Dry Ice International Cape Town Dry Ice for Sale in Cape Town 083 243 6483 info@dryice.co.za Unit 6, Aero Park, 80 Aviation Crescent, Airport City, Cape Town Dry Ice for Sale in Cape Town \u00a0 Call us on: 083 243 6483 \u00a0 Dry Ice International is proud to deliver high density, high quality dry ice [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":3218,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/3217"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dryice.co.za\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=3217"}],"version-history":